 digital products, and to interpret user test results, then design creative new solutions that yield better results. What You Will Do Partner with the product and the operation teams to define problems & goals, map user flows, prototype interactions, and manage design expectations Design elegant flows & interactions for a global audience across platforms Execute effectively in a fast-paced environment with ambiguity Champion design as a primary collaboration point for all disciplines Assess product testing results and team feedback and respond with design updates quickly and completely Assist with the creation of repurpose-able design assets and infrastructure Keep organized, well structured, design files Help create design system specifications and guidelines. What You Should Have: Minimum 5 years of collaborative experience in the capacity of designer of visual and user experience design Strong design portfolio (should contain real business examples and may contain person work) Proficient in Xd or equivalent design tool Proficiency with prototyping both Lo-fi & hi-fi experiences Proficiency in Adobe illustrator and photoshop Have contributed on a team as a designer with strong collaboration Demonstrate experience sufficient enough to understand common software development processes, challenges, and needs Demonstrates prioritization of quality and completion over convenience and ease Effective and clear communicator and team collaborator Ability to communicate design philosophy, reasoning, and decisions to teams Demonstrate working knowledge of typography, photography, illustration, color and design Ability to work and thrive in a fast-paced team environment Culturally aware and continuously interested in developing design skills to stay abreast of the latest relevant trends What We Hope You Have: Proficiency in Framer, protopie, origami studio, or other prototype tools Animation skills 3d software experience Adobe After Effects experience HTML, CSS, and other fron